@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Brikabrak" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Brikabrak runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  Playing is quite simple, just click on any tile, two of the tiles
located on either side or diagonally next to it will exchange
(swap) their positions. These tiles are the ones that are
positioned according to the arrows shown at the right of the game
board. If you click on a tile that is located on the edge of the
game board, that tile will exchange its position with the one
immediately next to it, again, in the direction shown by the
arrows.

  The goal is also very simple: place as many tiles of the same
type together, it is not important that they make a horizontal or
diagonal series of tiles of the same type. What is important is
that all these tiles are 'touching', either horizontally or
diagonally, each other...

  You get 1 point for 3 tiles of the same type that are placed
together. The number of points increases to 2, 4, 8 points, and so
on, as 4 or more tiles of the same type are placed next to each
other... But that does not end there: for more than 3 tiles of the
same type together, the total of points is then multiplied by 5,
which is a bonus multiplier for the game. When you clear up the
board, that is, no tile with any pattern remains; the game will
display a new board and the bonus multiplier will be increased to
10, and then 20, 40... up to 160, for subsequently completed game
boards...

  When you place together a number of tiles of the same type, the
pattern that are shown on the tiles will be removed and the empty
tiles can be moved like the other tiles.

  Last but not least: never let only 1 or 2 tiles with a pattern of
any type remain on the game board, as that would eventually end the
game...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

